                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#181v">f. 181v</locus>
                           <desc>: Excerpt from the prayer Barǝkännä ʾǝgziʾǝnä... “Bless us Our
                              Lord...” and an offering prayer over the bread and wine.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#181v">181v</locus>: ...ሐዋርያት፡ ባርከነ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ባርከነ፡
                              በበረከተ፡ ጻድቃን፡ ወሰማዕታት፡ ባርከነ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ባርከነ፡ በበረከተ፡ ካህናት፡...</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> The prayer is written in the same well-trained hand as the
                              corrections. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- The Pss. are divided into groups of ten or thirty
                           separated by a crude zigzag, drawn in pencil. Also, a zigzag occurs at
                           the beginning of Text I-2.
 - Indication concerning the special
                           occasions when Ps. 3 could be read: ሶበ፡ ትፈቱ፡ ሢመተ፡ አንብብ፡ ለርእሰከ፡ is
                           written, in a secondary hand, in ink, on <locus target="#3r">3r</locus>.
                           
 - The scribe reduced the size of his handwriting to accommodate the
                           whole line: <locus target="#123v">123v</locus>, 124v, 125r, 126rv, 132r,
                           138r.
 - Part of the line is taken up: e.g., <locus target="#9r">9r</locus>, 34r, 52r, 64v, 72r, 78v, 81v, 87v, 91r, 97v, 99v, 145v,
                           150r, 157r, 163v, 165v.
 - Part of the line is taken down: e.g.,
                              <locus target="#37r">37r</locus>, 39r, 46v, 64r, 78r, 81r, 100v,
                           101v.
 - Tamallas-sign, in the shape of a cross, indicating the place
                           where the omission, written in the upper margin, belongs: <locus target="#56v">56v</locus> l.10.
 - Numerous corrections written
                           over erasures, most probably in a secondary hand: e.g., <locus target="#5r">5r</locus>, 15r, 20r, 34v, 53v, 65r, 81v, 90v, 109v,
                           121v, 152v.
 - Erasures marked with two or three lines: e.g., <locus target="#9v">9v</locus>, 14v, 21v, 24r, 37r, 57v, 60v, 79r, 88v,
                           133r.
 - Line or several lines of a text have been rubbed out: <locus from="152r" to="153v">152r-153v</locus>, 161v, 176ra, 177rb.
 - A
                           few lines of Ps. 1 are written on <locus target="#1r">1r</locus>. 
 -
                           A few lines from the offering prayer (s. Additio 1) and a legend for the
                           drawing written twice; written upside down: <locus target="#182r">182r</locus>.
 - Title of the Ps. written in a secondary hand:
                              <locus target="#10v">10v</locus>, 40v. 
 - Words መዝሙር ፱ and መዝሙር፲
                           written in red pen: <locus target="#7r">7r</locus>, 9r.
 - Scribbles
                           and doodles, in pen and pencil: <locus target="#1r">1r</locus>, 2r, 4r,
                           4v, 13v, 14r, 20v, 21r, 22v, 25v, 33r, 42v, 60v, 107v, 125v, 137v, 138v,
                           170v, 175v, 176r, 176v, 177r, 178v, 179r, 180r, 181v, 182v.</item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- Daily readings of Text I-2 are indicated by the
                              days of the week written in the upper margin, in pen: fols. 156r,
                              156v, 157r. - Daily readings of Text I-4 are indicated by the days of
                              the week crudely written in the upper margin, in pen: fols. 166v,
                              168v, 170v, 172v, 173v, 174v. - A red thread is inserted in the upper
                              margin of fols. 96, 124, 142.</desc>
                        </item>
